Harter v. Board of Commissioners of Boone County. [No. 9,511. From Boone Circuit Court; Willett H. Parr, Judge. Action by Samuel W. Harter against the Board of Commissioners of Boone county. *702L. Ert Slack, Willis C. Nusbaum and Miller & Dowling, for appellants. Roy Ardney, for appellee.

Cause transferred to Supreme Court November 28, 1916.]

Transferred to Supreme Court.

[Reporter’s Note. — This cause was transferred to the Supreme Court by the Appellate Court under the provisions of §1604 Burns 1014, Acts 1001 p. 565, with recommendations by Felt, J. The opinion of the Supreme Court on the auestions involved is reported in Harter v. Board, etc,, 186 Ind.-, 116 N. E. 304.]
